snippet.title: 70 | Amber Vilhauer | It‘s Not Business, It‘s Personal
snippet.description:
Source:
https://www.podbean.com/eau/pb-638jz-1155e92

Today's edition of The Greatness Machine marks our 100th episode! Darius chats with Amber Vilhauer, an online digital marketing expert who supports authors, speakers and coaches to establish a powerful, integrated online presence that gets results and empowers them to make a difference in their industry.
 
Since starting her agency, NGNG Enterprises (standing for No Guts No Glory) in 2007, she has spent her career impacting her community and building strong strategic alliances with industry leaders and game-changers across the web. 
 
Amber has supported more than one thousand entrepreneurs on six continents to get results. She has been the launch manager behind dozens of #1 bestselling books including those for Mark Victor Hansen, Brendon Burchard, Lisa Nichols and Les Brown.
 
You'll discover which is harder: launching a book or starting a company?
 
You'll learn about a terrifying, yet empowering story from Amber's past.
 
You'll also discover the question you really need to be asking yourself when it comes to goal setting.
 
Join Darius and Amber for this inspiring and uplifting episode, marking 100 such amazing conversations!
 
Enjoy!

What You'll Learn in this Show:
Which is harder: launching a book or starting a company?
A terrifying, yet empowering story from Amber's past.
The question you really need to be asking yourself when it comes to goal setting. 
And so much more...
